events.name: New York Knicks at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 34 points, Collin Sexton had four 3-pointers in the fourth quarter and the Utah Jazz ran past the New York Knicks 121-106 on Saturday to snap a four-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 34 points and Sexton hits 4 4th-quarter 3s to help Jazz bury Knicks 121-106

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 30 points, nine rebounds and eight assists, and the Orlando Magic beat the Detroit Pistons 111-100 Saturday night for their eighth win in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Pistons 111-100 behind Franz Wagner's 30 points

headlines.description: — Scotty Pippen Jr. had a career-best 30 points with 10 assists to lead the Memphis Grizzlies past the Chicago Bulls 142-131 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scotty Pippen Jr. scores career-high 30 points in Grizzlies' 142-131 win over Bulls

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 25 points and Shaedon Sharpe added 24 as the Portland Trail Blazers bounced back from a tough loss with a 104-98 win over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons scores 25, Sharpe adds 24 as Trail Blazers bounce back with 104-98 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 32 points and 11 rebounds and Damian Lillard added 31 points to lead the Milwaukee Bucks past the Charlotte Hornets 125-119 on Saturday night for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball's career-high 50 points not enough as Antetokounmpo, Lillard lead Bucks past Hornets 125-119

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 25 points, Harrison Barnes had 22 and the San Antonio Spurs overcame a 17-point third-quarter deficit to beat the Golden State Warriors 104-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama returns from three-game absence to help Spurs rally past Warriors, 104-94

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 34 points and Michael Porter Jr. added 24 as the Denver Nuggets used a strong second half to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 127-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic score 34, Porter adds 24 as Nuggets use strong second half to beat Lakers 127-102
